J-HOST HELP
This script helps manage JAssist Hosting Servers and Hosting functionalities

Usage: sudo jhost [-[option1] [options1-1] [options1-2] ...] [-[option2] [options2-1 [options2-2] ...]]

  No input:
    The initiation script will be run: system packages will be updated, timezone will be set, etc.

  -option:
      -i: install webserver on the system
          It takes one argument from below options:
            (n)ginx: installs the Nginx webserver and related packages (LEMP)
            (a)pache: installs the Apache webserver and related packages (LAMP)
      -b: create system backup
          It takes one argument, a host name to create backup from that specific host or
          no argument which will create full system backup.
      -h: prints this help screen
      -v: prints version of the scripts

For more please read README.md
